messageBody:
I have yet to study the Quikscript Manual which I only downloaded this week;
I learned QS through Coles Funny Picture Book no. 2 back in 1979 and have
been using it since then.

Regarding numbers, I will be interested to learn the 'right' or standard way
of doing this. So that I do not confuse my QS numbers with letters, I have
always used < and > as brackets around my number characters. Works well for
me, though I am sure there are other methods which I will learn as I study
the manual.


shemwat
